01/12/2004
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Prime Minister-designate Vlado Buckovski plans certain changes in the structure of the government, including the introduction of four deputy prime minister positions for strategic sectors -- economy, the political system, EU integration and implementation of the Ohrid Accords.
According to press reports, the ruling coalition partners -- Buckovski's Social Democratic Alliance of Macedonia, the Liberal Democratic Party and the Democratic Union for Integration -- have entered the final phase of negotiations regarding the composition of the cabinet.
In other news, Abdulmenaf Bexheti resigned as leader of the opposition ethnic Albanian Party for Democratic Prosperity.
He cited personal reasons.
(Utrinski Vesnik, Dnevnik, Vest - 01/12/04;
A1 TV - 30/11/04)
